rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about bestowals of a coat of arms, viz. who received it, who granted it, what the coat of arms is, and the time frame when the coat of arms is used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Armorial Grant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the person, city, country, family etc. which received the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Armiger

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the coat of arms that was granted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the authority that grants the use of the coat of arms to the bearer. Note that this property is used only in cases where an agent grants the use of a coat of arms to the bearer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Granted by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date on which the coat of arms was first used by this bearer or on which the authority (if one exists) granted the coat of arms to the bearer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Used from

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date on which the authority revoked its grant or on which the bearer stopped using the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Used until

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A symbol consisting of a shield and other figures that represents a person, family, group or organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a coat of arms to information about the person, family, organisation, country, town etc. that holds the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bearers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to a symbol that is used to distinguish a branch of a family from the senior line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brisures

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to information about the main image on the shield of the coat of arms. Note that this property should not be used to provide information about the supporters, crest, etc. around the main image on the shield.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Charges

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to a symbol that is used in the compartment, if any, of the coat of arms. The compartment is the area directly below the sinister supporter on a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compartment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to the symbol directly above the shield of a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coronet

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to the top-most symbol on a coat of arms, the one directly below the motto.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Crest

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a coat of arms to a symbol of a helmet that is displayed between the crest and the coronet on the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Helm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a coat of arms to information about the patterns and coloring used in the shield of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Division of the Field

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a coat of arms to the symbol of a stylized cloak hanging from the helmet of the coat of arms. Note that the expected type of this property should be changed to symbols.heraldic_tincture.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mantling

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a coat of arms to another coat of arms that it displays.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Marshaled into

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a coat of arms to another coat of arms that is displayed on it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Marshalled Coats of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to a phrase, often in Latin, that describes the mission of the bearer of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Motto

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to a society or fellowship of knights that is associated with the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Order

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to information about the large rectilinear symbol on the shield of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ordinaire

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to the main image(s)to the left and/or right of the shield of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Supporter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a coat of arms to the color of the fabric displayed between the helm and the crest on the coat of arms. Note that the expected type of this property should eventually be changed to symbols.heraldic_tincture.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Torse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person, family, group, or other agent that holds a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms Bearer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a bearer of a coat of arms to information about the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms Used

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A piece of fabric with a particular design and set of colors that is used as a symbol of something.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flag

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a flag to the date that the flag was adopted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Adopted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a flag to one of the colors used on the flag. For example, the flag of the United States uses the colors red, white, and blue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Colors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a flag to one of the things represented on the flag. For example, the flags of the United States and the People's Republic of China both depict stars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Depicts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a flag to a person who designed the flag.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a flag to a standard descriptor for a use of the flag, e.g. national flag, civil flag, state flag, civil ensign, state ensign, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flag Use

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a flag to a ratio expressing the relative width and height of the flag.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Proportion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a flag to a thing represented by the flag, e.g. a political division, such as a country, state, province or city; an armed force or military unit; an organization such as a government agency or NGO; or a political office, such as head of state.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Referent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: This type is for any entity that is represented by a flag. Examples include political divisions, such as countries, states, provinces, and cities; militaries and military units; organizations, such as government agencies and NGOs; and political offices, such as heads of state.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flag referent
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. Just use mso:type.object instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for a uses of flags, e.g. national flag, civil flag, state flag, civil ensign, state ensign, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flag use

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A flag that refers to or is used by this entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flag

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The entity that this flag refers to or is used by.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flag user

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A symbol that is part of a coat of arms and is used to distinguish a branch of a family from the senior line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Brisure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a brisure to a coat of arms that contains the brisure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The main image on a shield of a coat of arms. Note that the charge is different from the supporters, crest, and other images that flank the shield on a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Charge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a heraldic charge to a coat of arms that depicts the charge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about heraldic charges, viz. their colors, referents, and the coats of arms on which they appear.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Charge Tincture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the referent of the charge displayed on the coat of arms, e.g. lion, cactus, maple leaf, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Charge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies a coat of arms on which the charge appears.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the color of the charge, as used on the given coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tincture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A symbol that is used in the compartment of a coat of arms. The compartment is the area directly below the sinister supporter on a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Compartment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a heraldic compartment to a coat of arms that contains the compartment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A symbol on a coat of arms that is directly above the shield of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Coronet

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a heraldic coronet to a coat of arms that contains the coronet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a heraldic coronet to the noble rank signified by the coronet when displayed on a coat of arms
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Noble Rank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The top-most symbol on a coat of arms, the one directly below the motto.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Crest

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a heraldic crest to a coat of arms that contains the crest.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A symbol of a helmet that is displayed between the crest and the coronet on a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Helm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a heraldic helm to a coat of arms that contains the helm.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms
Heraldic Mantling
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. The property symbols.coat_of_arms.mantling can be used to connect a coat of arms directly to the color of the mantling. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:symbols.coat_of_arms.mantling]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: coat_of_arms
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type symbols.heraldic_mantling is not needed. The property symbols.coat_of_arms.mantling can be used to connect a coat of arms directly to the color of the mantling. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:symbols.coat_of_arms.mantling]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The color of the mantling
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tincture
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type symbols.heraldic_mantling is not needed. The property symbols.coat_of_arms.mantling can be used to connect a coat of arms directly to the color of the mantling. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:symbols.coat_of_arms.mantling]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the large rectilinear symbol on the shield of a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Ordinaire

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a heraldic ordinaire to information about the coats of arms where it appears and its colors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the large rectilinear symbol on the shield of a coat of arms, viz. its color and shape.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Ordinaire Tincture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the ordinaire displayed on the given coat of arms
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ordinaire

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the color of the ordinaire.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tincture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The main symbols to the left and/or right of the shield of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Supporter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a heraldic supporter to a coat of arms in which the supporter appears.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the colors used on coats of arms, e.g. Bleu Celeste, Azure, and Tenne.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Tincture
Heraldic Torse
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. The property symbols.coat_of_arms.torse can be used to connect a coat of arms directly to the color of the torse. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:symbols.coat_of_arms.torse]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: coat_of_arms
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type symbols.heraldic_torse is not needed. The property symbols.coat_of_arms.torse can be used to connect a coat of arms directly to the color of the torse. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:symbols.coat_of_arms.torse]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The color of the torse
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tincture
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type symbols.heraldic_torse is not needed. The property symbols.coat_of_arms.torse can be used to connect a coat of arms directly to the color of the torse. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:symbols.coat_of_arms.torse]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for patterns used in the shield of a coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Variation of the Field

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a coat of arms to a standard descriptor of a pattern that is used in the shield of the coat of arms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the patterns used in the shield of a coat of arms, viz. the pattern, the color, and the coats of arms where the patterns appear.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldic Variation of the Field Tincture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a coat of arms where the heraldic variation of the field is used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat of Arms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the pattern by which the shield, or field, of a coat of arms is broken into distinct areas of color.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Variation of the Field

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the colors used in the backgrounds of the given heraldic divisions of the field.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tincture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization that is authorized to grant coats of arms to people, families, groups, and/or other agents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heraldry Granting Body

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a heraldry granting body to information about the coats of arms bestowed by the group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coats of Arms Granted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person or thing that has other things named after him/her/it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Name source
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. Just use type.object instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person or thing that's named after something else.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Namesake
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. Just use type.object instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: What this entity was named after.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Named after
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to type.object. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]
